This paper is primarily focused on semantic image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new neural network architecture, which involves optimization and approximation techniques, which are also studied in the neural networks (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
